{
  "style": "APA",
  "texts": [
    "Alsuradi et al. (2020) trained two Extreme Gradient Boosting (XGBoost) (Chen and Guestrin, 2016) classifiers followed by Shapley values on the beta band power spectral densities (PSD) in an active touch task distinguishing trials with and without haptic feedback.",
    "The first classifier aimed to identify the most influential channel using a combination of peak value and latency, while the second was trained directly on beta band PSD data of the identified channel to determine the most important time period.",
    "The study found that a frontal electrode was the most important channel and that the peak after approximately 700 ms, more pronounced in trials with haptic feedback, was the most important time period.",
    "These results align with previous studies and confirm the importance of the beta band for such tasks, as well as the ability of SHAP to deal with highly correlated features.",
    "While there are a few approaches combining ML or DL with XAI and in the case of the last mentioned study (Alsuradi et al., 2020) even findings from typical conventional EEG analyses could be corroborated, to the best of our knowledge, we are the first to use this combination of methods to detect ERP components objectively."
  ],
  "correct_citations": [
